description: Dr. Dave is a PBIA Master Instructor and an instructional author. Dr. Dave is also a long-time monthly instructional columnist for Billiards Digest magazine and an active participant in online billiards forums and social media. He is a devoted authority and an expert in understanding and teaching the physics of the game. Dr. Dave offers private lessons and intensive courses through Dr. Dave’s Pool School and the BU Boot Camps.

description:
"Do or Die" is a English idiomatic expression that means:

- A situation where someone must succeed or face severe consequences
- A critical moment where failure is not an option
- A situation where one must give their best effort to achieve something

In Hindi, the phrase "Do or Die" can be translated to:

- "करो या मरो" (Karo ya Maro)
- "जीतो या हारो" (Jito ya Haro)
- "सफल होना ही है" (Safal Hona Hi Hai)

The phrase is often used in situations where someone is faced with a significant challenge or a high-stakes decision, and they must muster all their strength and resources to succeed.

description:
Family owned sawmill business, started over 30 years ago. Located outside Portland, Oregon. We carry hundreds of black walnut slabs, redwood, oak, maple and other species. We cut, air dry 2+ years for hardwoods, and kiln dry all our slabs unless otherwise specified and then flatten them.

We also offer milling by the hour for slabbing or dimensional lumber, from our wood-Mizer LT-50 bandsaw mill and Lucas slabbing mill, from your own logs, along with kiln drying and beam planing services. 

We also take custom orders, for things such as large beams, siding, decking,  beam wrap, flooring, paneling, and and other products, using Doug fir and western red cedar from logs we have which are FSC certified. We also  offer reclaimed beams and lumber and slab flattening and sanding, along with offering about any other custom wood product you could need. 
You can check out our website for more info.

Demetrius “Juice” Deason                                
             Comedian. Hero. Legend. 
It has been said that legends are made, not born. 
It’s also been said that heroes come from unlikely places. 
What has not been said – until now - is how a lay up and never giving up can lead to stand up. 
The fastest rising star and hardest working man in comedy, Demetrius “Juice” Deason, grew up in a South Central LA motel room with his mother, sister and brother and had learning difficulties so severe that sometimes he was embarrassed to speak. 


Comedian Juices is all about Nipsey’s mentality to Reach One Teach One. 
So each video posted on this page is either 2 inspire, teach, make laugh, or just share some real life game 💯💯
